Package: amelie
Type: Package
Title: Anomaly Detection with Normal Probability Functions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person("Dmitriy", "Bolotov", email = "dbolotov@live.com", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Implements anomaly detection as binary classification for cross-sectional data. 
Uses maximum likelihood estimates and normal probability functions to classify observations as anomalous.
The method is presented in the Machine Learning course by Andrew Ng: https://www.coursera.org/learn/machine-learning.
Imports: stats
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
